#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
================================================================================
  V01D MASTER SDK  —  Launcher  (single-file edition)

  ONE Python file. Standard library only (tkinter is included with Python).
  Zero dependencies. Fully offline. No internet, no installer, no pip.

  HOW IT WORKS
    The 15 bundled apps ("carts") are EMBEDDED at the bottom of this file
    as a plain JSON string (look for EMBEDDED_CARTS_JSON near the end).
    Each cart's source code is stored as a plain text field — NO base64,
    NO compression, NO encoded blobs. You can scroll to the bottom of
    this file and read every line of every cart.

    User-built carts get saved as individual .json files in
    ~/v01d_workspace/user_carts/, using the same simple schema.

    Cart JSON schema:
        {
          "id":       "my_cart",
          "title":    "My Cart",
          "author":   "you",
          "genre":    "Game",
          "version":  "1.0",
          "tag":      "tool",
          "icon":     "■",
          "desc":     "What this does...",
          "source":   "import tkinter ... # the whole .py file as a string",
          "checksum": "<first 16 hex chars of sha256(source bytes)>",
          "size":     12345
        }

  HOW TO ADD YOUR OWN CART
    Easiest: open the WORKSHOP tab, paste your code, fill in the form, and
    click "BUILD CART". The launcher writes the JSON to your user folder.

    Manually: create `<id>.json` in `carts/` with the schema above. The
    launcher will compute the checksum on first load and warn you if you
    forgot it. Filenames must match `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+`.

  WORKSPACE FOLDERS  (created in your home folder on first run)
        ~/v01d_workspace/scripts/    IDE working files
        ~/v01d_workspace/exports/    Library "Export .py" target
        ~/v01d_workspace/user_carts/ Workshop "Build Cart" target

================================================================================
  SECURITY NOTES — please read.

  This program runs Python code from the carts you load. Running Python is
  fundamentally arbitrary code execution. There is no sandbox. Honest list
  of what's protected and what isn't:

    1. Every cart records a SHA-256 checksum. Before running, the launcher
       recomputes and warns if it changed. Catches accidental edits, not a
       determined attacker.
    2. All `subprocess.Popen` calls use list-form arguments — never
       `shell=True` — so filenames cannot inject shell commands.
    3. Cart IDs and any user-supplied filename must match
       `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+`. No path separators, no dots, no spaces.
    4. We never `eval()` or `exec()` cart source in the launcher process;
       carts always run as a separate `python` subprocess.
    5. Cart JSON files that look malformed are skipped, not executed.

  We do NOT claim "airtight" security. If you load a malicious cart, it
  runs with your user permissions like any other Python script. Treat
  carts the same way you'd treat any downloaded program.
================================================================================
"""

# ─── Standard-library imports only.  Nothing from pip. ────────────────────
